  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dc4\u0dc3\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dd0\u0db8\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dda\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0da2\u0dcf\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0d9c\u0dd3\u0dba \u0daf\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dc5 \u0db6\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0dba\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dda \u0dc0\u0dbb\u0daf\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "There is nothing wrong in singing the national anthem in Tamil during the Independence Day celebrations",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Cabinet Spokesman, Minister of Transport, Highways and Mass Media Dr. Bandula Gunawardena said that there is no problem in singing the National Anthem in Tamil during the 75th Independence Day celebrations in the country next February.",
        "The minister said that the National Anthem has been sung in the previous Independence Day celebrations in the official languages \u200b\u200bof the country, Sinhala and Tamil.",
        "Mr. Gunawardena said that the cabinet also approved the establishment of a cabinet sub-committee of eight ministers with the president and the prime minister to organize the activities of the 75th Independence Day celebrations.",
        "The minister said this in response to a question raised by a journalist at the cabinet decision notification press conference held today (16) at the Government Information Department."
      ],
